cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel method for embedding nonvectorial graph data into vector spaces for machine learning and pattern classification tasks. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and can also be applied to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) tasks. The method involves parsing and sampling graphlets, which can be seen as a form of data structure (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the use of maximum margin classifiers, which are commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
